{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f69cfd6d-00f9-40bd-9d00-14a84b27bb67","content":"The project doesn't exist yet at that path, but here's how to configure `mcp.json` for a C# MCP server using **stdio** transport (the standard for VS Code agent mode):\n\nCreate `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\n        \"run\",\n        \"--project\",\n        \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- **`command: \"dotnet\"`** with `\"run\"` in `args` builds and launches your project.\n- For a **published** binary, replace with `\"command\": \"path/to/MyMcpServer\"` and remove the `run`/`--project` args.\n- Your C# server must read JSON-RPC from **stdin** and write responses to **stdout** (e.g., using the `ModelContextProtocol` or `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` MCP SDK).\n- Make sure **no** diagnostic or log output goes to stdout — use stderr for logging.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5cc656e1-d64e-4461-9294-e07b1612766d","outputTokens":317,"requestId":"D031:DAA94:14C7D27:1742DD5:6A0673BC"},"id":"292c38cd-75ff-4616-8806-e299e88a85ec","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:15:49.923Z","parentId":"7435ef7c-3631-4bf9-a0ee-76365b308835"}
